properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 3 at 10:13PM CST until February 4 at 6:00AM CST by NWS North Platte NE
properties.description:
...LIGHT SNOW WILL DEVELOP EASTWARD THIS EVENING AND OVERNIGHT...

.A strong winter storm across the Rockies will continue to move
out onto the Plains through Tuesday and will bring mainly light
snow across the western half of Nebraska.

* WHAT...Snow is expected with total snow accumulations of 1 to
3 inches.

* WHERE...Sheridan and Western Cherry Counties.

* WHEN...From noon CST /11 AM MST/ Monday to 6 AM CST /5 AM MST/
Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute. Visibilities could
be reduced to 1 mile at times.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Wind chill readings of 5 above to 5 below
zero are possible by Tuesday morning.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

Call Nebraska 511 for the latest road information.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM CST /5 AM MST/ TUESDAY
